news.title: Uttar Pradesh government to draw up SOPs to simplify handover process of townships
news.para: While regulations require that townships be transferred to local civic bodies once they are developed, delays are caused due to incomplete work, developers' reluctance to hand over projects, and disputes between authorities, like in Indirapuram.

news.title: Delhi HC approves demolition of Signature View Apartments
news.para: Delhi High Court on Monday cleared the way for its demolition by Delhi Development Authority and gave three months for the remaining residents to vacate it.

news.title: ADB commits $70 million to Vastu Housing Finance for affordable housing
news.para: The loan will enhance access to affordable and sustainable housing loans for underserved borrowers, with 15 per cent of the funds allocated specifically to first-time borrowers, Vastu Housing Finance said in a statement.

news.title: Bengaluru development body set to develop six layouts with 50,000 sites
news.para: Confirming this, BDA commissioner Jayaram N said, "The cost of acquiring land is very high, and our land acquisition act is not very compensation-friendly."

news.title: Centre approved 6.5 lakh houses under PMAY for state: Maharashtra CM
news.para: Speaking to reporters, Fadnavis described the initiative as "historic," stating that 26 lakh people have registered for the scheme, of whom 20 lakh will be provided houses.

news.title: UPPCB recommends stoppage of construction of four housing projects in Noida
news.para: In Nov, show-cause notices were issued to five projects and only one of them in Surajpur Site C could produce NOCs issued by the pollution control board, UPPCB regional officer (Greater Noida) DK Gupta said.

news.title: Oberoi Realty to develop 81.05 acres land in Alibaug
news.para: Oberoi Realty intends to construct approximately 150 high end residential villas and a high-end luxury star hotel/ resort on the land.

news.title: Almost 80% allottees didn’t get possession of land off Yamuna Expressway: CAG
news.para: Even for those where registries went through, there was no industrial unit on these land parcels that became operational at least till Apr 2022, the auditor said in its report. Land allotted in other categories was also similarly affected.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP cracks down on illegal commercial activities in DLF phase 3
news.para: Acting on the orders of the Punjab and Haryana high court, enforcement teams issued show-cause notices to over 300 property owners, marking a significant move to curb violations in the area.

news.title: Signature View Apartments' residents laud Delhi HC's direction to pay rent as soon as flats are vacated
news.para: Residents also welcomed the court's decision to pay a facilitation amount or rent at the rate of Rs 50,000 per month to the owners of HIG flats and Rs 38,000 per month for the MIG flats from the date when a flat is vacated and enhance the rate by 10% per annum.

news.title: Ventive Hospitality IPO gets subscribed 1.28 times on day two of bidding
news.para: Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) portion attracted 1.76 times subscription, while the quota for Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) got subscribed 1.22 times. The Non-Institutional Investors part received 1.07 times subscription.

news.title: Gujarat RERA introduces new banking rules for developers
news.para: According to the new rules, developers will need to maintain three bank accounts for a project to ensure transparency in financial transactions.

news.title: Sebi to auction 28 properties of five companies to recover investor money
news.para: The properties will be auctioned for a reserve price of Rs 28.66 crore. Ravi Kiran Realty India, Mangalam Agro Products , and Purusattam Infotech Industries are the other companies, whose properties will be auctioned.

news.title: Office demand continues to scale-up in 2024
news.para: At India level, 2024 is likely to see Grade A absorption breach 60 million sq feet for the first time in the office market of the country.

news.title: Norway's wealth fund acquires full ownership of eight US properties for $976.8 million
news.para: "In a period of heightened dislocation in the office sector, we see this as an opportune moment to invest," said Per Loeken, the fund's global co-head of unlisted real estate.

news.title: Residential realty demand, supply growth to remain steady this fiscal
news.para: Demand growth in the last two fiscals was resilient on account of factors such as favourable macroeconomic conditions and the rise in household income levels outpacing the appreciation in housing capital values.

news.title: OYO acquires G6 Hospitality for $525 million
news.para: On September 20, OYO agreed to acquire US-based G6 Hospitality, the parent company of the Motel 6 and Studio 6 brands, in an all-cash transaction.

news.title: Mall vacancy levels down to 8.3% in H1 FY25: Report
news.para: The demand was higher than supply for the third consecutive year; over 3.1 million sq ft retail space leased in H1 2024.

news.title: Developers to launch 253.16 million sq ft of new supply over next few years: Anarock
news.para: Of this total planned supply, just 23% (approx. 57.15 million sq ft) were launched in H1 FY 2025.
